description:
In 1891, Ellen White was called to go to Australia by the General Conference, but she was unsure if this was in God's will. She was willing to go, and her decision to visit would prove to be a great blessing to the reformation work in Australia, New Zealand, and the South Pacific. 

To find out more information about Ellen White's journey to Australia read our extended article on our website.
